\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. erecta} (Hudson) Coville, {\i Contr. U.S. Nat. Herb.}{\b  4}: 115 (1893) ({\i Sium angustifolium} L., {\i S. erectum} Hudson). Stoloniferous, glabrous perennial 30-100 cm. Submerged leaves 3- to 4-pinnate with linear lobes; lower aerial leaves with (5-)7-14(-19) pairs of sessile, oblong-lanceolate to ovate, biserrate segments 2-6 cm upper cauline leaves small, usually very irregularly serrate. Umbels leaf-opposed; rays 10-20. Bracts and bracteoles numerous, often leaf-like and 3-fid or pinnatisect. Fruit 1·5-2 mm, usually wider than long. 2n = 20.{\i  In shallow water. Almost throughout Europe except the extreme north.} All except Az Cr Fa Fe Is Rs (N) Sb Tu.
